      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm studying for my con law exam and i'm a bit stuck. can u explain the main arguments people use to support originalism in constitutional interpretation?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! Originalists argue that the Constitution's meaning was fixed at the time of its enactment, reflecting the intent of the Framers. They believe it's imperative to adhere strictly to this original meaning to maintain the rule of law and democratic principles. Originalists fear that changing interpretations over time might lead to judicial activism, where judges effectively write new laws rather than simply interpreting existing ones. To them, this approach ensures consistency, legal stability, and adherence to the democratic process, since elected representatives, not judges, are the ones creating new laws.",
